# Local Network Web Application Penetration Testing Lab (LN-WAPT Lab)

## Overview
Hands-on cybersecurity lab simulating real-world internal network web application attacks. 
Designed for VAPT practice, CEH Practical preparation, and bug bounty workflows in a safe lab environment.

##  Objectives
- Understand internal web attack surfaces
- Perform full web application pentesting lifecycle
- Practice industry-standard tools
- Prepare for CEH Practical & real pentesting

## Lab Architecture
### Attacker
- Kali Linux / Parrot OS

### Targets
- DVWA
- OWASP Juice Shop
- Metasploitable2
- Custom vulnerable PHP app

### Network
- VirtualBox / VMware
- NAT + Host-only
- Same subnet (192.168.56.0/24)

## Tools Used
Nmap, Burp Suite, Nikto, SQLmap, Metasploit, Gobuster, Wireshark, Hydra, Netcat

##  Methodology
### Network Discovery
```bash
ip a
netdiscover -r 192.168.56.0/24
nmap -sn 192.168.56.0/24
